<div id="review_3476903127" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3476903127" />
    <a title="Michael Engel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66625507-michael-engel"><img alt="Michael Engel" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3476903127?book_show_action=true">Aug 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Engel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Engel" href="/user/show/66625507-michael-engel">Michael Engel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3476903127" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9437380397282665539">I am at a loss to understand all the good reviews. I have a strong interest and a lot of knowledge in this subject, and I found the entire premise of her book to be historically absurd. I got about 50 pages into it and gave up. She seems to imply that Vienna would have been a refuge for Jews in 1939, when in fact it was part of the Reich by then. And the Nazis would hardly have kidnapped half-Jewish children in 1940 (who were known as &quot;mischlinge&quot;--&quot;mixed breeds&quot;) for training in an elite Nazi s</span>
  <span id="freeText9437380397282665539" style="display:none">I am at a loss to understand all the good reviews. I have a strong interest and a lot of knowledge in this subject, and I found the entire premise of her book to be historically absurd. I got about 50 pages into it and gave up. She seems to imply that Vienna would have been a refuge for Jews in 1939, when in fact it was part of the Reich by then. And the Nazis would hardly have kidnapped half-Jewish children in 1940 (who were known as "mischlinge"--"mixed breeds") for training in an elite Nazi school. (They did have breeding centers for SS men to mate with "Aryan" women, which were called "Lebensborn" centers). And what Jew in Germany would have worn a Star of David around his neck to go into a store where Jews weren't welcome? And that's just the beginning of the book! The writing is tedious, the story is choppy, the dialogue unreal, and quickly becomes tiresome. There are hundreds of great books based on life in Nazi Germany. This is most definitely not one of them. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9437380397282665539" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


