<div id="review_3464882264" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3464882264" />
    <a title="Shanda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/119020617-shanda"><img alt="Shanda" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3464882264?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shanda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shanda" href="/user/show/119020617-shanda">Shanda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3464882264" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3206439648417079119">The Boy Who Saw In Colours tells the inspiring story of a young painter who was chosen for an elite Nazi school during the years of the Third Reich.<br/><br/>The writing and prose of the novel were beautiful and the author used metaphors that work perfectly. The characters are the real stars of this novel, as the story is simply life. Albeit, a very tough life that is incredibly interesting. Robinson tackles real-life issues that children still struggle with today, so in that sense, I recommend this novel</span>
  <span id="freeText3206439648417079119" style="display:none">The Boy Who Saw In Colours tells the inspiring story of a young painter who was chosen for an elite Nazi school during the years of the Third Reich.<br /><br />The writing and prose of the novel were beautiful and the author used metaphors that work perfectly. The characters are the real stars of this novel, as the story is simply life. Albeit, a very tough life that is incredibly interesting. Robinson tackles real-life issues that children still struggle with today, so in that sense, I recommend this novel to teenagers. Josef is charming and his persistence for doing what be loves is inspiring. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3206439648417079119" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


